In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, mix butter and brown sugar until creamy. Mix in egg and vinegar until well blended. Add flour, soda, and salt and mix on low speed until incorporated. Mix in pecans. Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets. Bake at 375 degrees F until flattened and uniformly browned, 7 to 9 minutes. They will be soft, but will firm up as they cool. Cool 1 minute and remove to racks. Store airtight or freeze.